Add the Omni-Channel Component to the Classic Console

After you get Omni-Channel all set up for your organization, itâ€™s time to add the Omni-Channel component to the Salesforce classic console so that your agents can start receiving work.

REQUIRED USER PERMISSIONS:
Customize Application
Available in: both Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience
Omni-Channel is available in: Essentials, Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

The Omni-Channel component appears in the bottom-right corner of the classic console. From there, agents can change their presence status and triage their incoming work assignments.

If your organization uses Chat, you can either use the Chat widget or the Omni-Channel component to manage chats, but not both.

From Setup, enter Apps in the Quick Find box, then select Apps.
Click Edit next to the classic console app that you want to add the Omni-Channel component to.
In the Choose Console Components section, add Omni-Channel to your list of selected items.
Click Save.
title: Adding Omni-Channel Component to Classic Console
